I want you all to meet Tyler who was born with 2 extra nipples.  I performed a surgical removal of the extra nipples on my TV show Dr. 90210.  I truly enjoyed getting to know Tyler who is a pre-med student and had a true interest in surgery and science and I am so excited for her future. 

Extra nipples or supernumerary nipples occur in 1-6% of the population and many people don’t even realize they have them since they usually get mistaken for a mole or birthmark in the armpit or on the chest or abdomen.  The extra nipples sit along the milk line - as they do with other mammals.

The extra nipples range in size from being very small to actually having breast tissue under them and in the majority of cases they are benign but it still important to get them checked out by a doctor like any other pigmented lesion. Many patients like Tyler do choose to have them removed for comfort reasons because sometimes they catch or rub on clothing.  They can easily be excised under local anesthesia and usually only a a few sutures are needed. #plasticsurgery #dr90210 @surgeon

Dr. Cat Begovic is a board-certified plastic surgeon in Los Angeles and Beverly Hills, California. She graduated from Harvard University with Honors in Molecular and Cellular biology. I wanted to share with you this stunning transformation of my patient @brookebarrows whose inspiring story was shared on Dr. 90210. Brooke lost over 200 pounds through diet and exercise - her tummy tuck to remove the excess remaining skin and tighten her abdominal wall was the finishing touch after all that hard work.  Her results are so natural, you can’t even tell she had surgery done. She is a successful plus sized model and models a lot of swimwear and two-piece outfits. When I performed this surgery - I took into consideration all the little details - keeping her scar thin and low and symmetric, creating my “signature natural looking belly button”, shaping her waist and abdomen to create the appearance of abs, and all the while keeping her curves.  Brooke - I feel so blessed to have you as my patient, thank you for being so inspiring, and I am so excited for all the amazing things your future holds. @surgeon

#dr90210 #plasticsurgeon #tummytuck

node.text:
I specialize in labiaplasty and vaginal rejuvenation.  For those of you who aren’t familiar with these terms, labiaplasty is a plastic surgery procedure that reduces and reshapes the labia minora.  Over 10 years ago I authored a book chapter on this topic, and then since then from doing hundreds of labiaplasties and studying the anatomy and aesthetics of this area, I have developed my very own surgical technique that creates a natural looking, tucked in, symmetric shape, little to no pain and an almost invisible scar. I often combine this with clitoral hood reduction in order to create an even and gentle curve that blends seamlessly.  

However what makes me a pioneer in vaginal cosmetic surgery is not just my surgical techniques, but more so that I have helped bring the topic of vaginal cosmetic surgery to the forefront of every day conversation.  Through my social media, you tube videos, and TV shows and media interviews on this topic, I have helped to make talking about vaginal cosmetic surgery not taboo.  Through educating the public on why women seek this surgery and creating a better understanding of what women can do to seek solutions for this area of the body, it has helped break the barrier of embarrassment related to this topic. Women who seek labiaplasty complain of discomfort because of rubbing or twisting of the labia, issues with hygiene, avoidance of leggings, swimwear or other tight fitting clothing, or because they feel self conscious during intimacy because of labial asymmetry or excess labial show and volume. It significantly improves the quality of life for women who seek this surgery. Im so proud of Jessi and I admire her courage for sharing her labiaplasty journey on Dr. 90210 #labiaplasty #thepussycatdolls

What is the difference between skin and fat?

My patient from Episode 3 of my show Dr. 90210 wanted to get her pre baby body back after pregnancy and thought she had a lot of abdominal fat after pregnancy but in fact it was mostly excess skin.

A tummy tuck repairs the abdominal muscles, tightens the abdominal wall and removes and tightens excess skin.  Liposuction removes and thins excess fat.

Ashley first had a tummy tuck and then liposuction of her back and waist with fat transfer to her butt.  She did not have liposuction to her abdomen.
You can see how the tummy tuck alone created a flat and contoured natural looking abdomen and using my special belly button technique she has a natural looking “innie” belly button with hidden scar.  Her tummy tuck incision is low and thin.  The liposuction with fat transfer accentuated the waist.  She has a beautiful result and I am so grateful to be her surgeon #dr90210 @surgeon #plasticsurgery #tummytuck

“Dr. Cat Begovic says her plastic surgery practice is “at least five times busier” than before “Dr. 90210” premiered amid the coronavirus pandemic.

The 43-year-old said her “mommy makeovers” — which include the midsection, body contouring, breast surgery and even vaginal cosmetic surgery — are in high demand.

“I think it’s more just because people are at home, they’re able to work from home, able to care for themselves a little better,” she told Page Six. “They had their caretaker with them usually, whereas normally they would have to block off a huge amount of time, make more arrangements in order to be able to recover from surgery. So I think that people being able to relax and rest and give themselves the time and care they need after surgery has made it definitely busier for plastic surgery in general.”

node.text:
A lot of you have asked me if Breast Implant Illness is a real thing.  Yes, it is very real and is devastating to the women who develop it.  I personally have had three close friends who had it and I know how much they went through.  Luckily none of my patients have developed it but my friends’ experiences as well as the recent Allergan breast implant recall truly shook me. I am so thankful I never placed any of the recalled implants in someone - just the thought having a recalled product in your body is scary.
I stopped doing breast augmentation for a while, for two reasons - I wanted to find out more information on my own and also listen to the experiences of more women who have suffered from BII. I also don’t want to glorify breast implants while so many women are suffering and not being heard. That’s the reason why I didn’t do any breast augmentation surgeries or breast implants on my TV show Dr. 90210.
I discuss all the potential risks with my patients, long term effects, and also let them know that there is a lot we don’t know about implants and there is an ongoing research. The FDA recently came out with new black box warnings for breast implants and I make sure that every patient is educated and aware of possible side effects. I also send everyone to platforms and pages such as @breast_implant_illness where women share their stories and experiences with breast implants illness as well as where to get help. These groups have done a lot for women to educate themselves and advocate for themselves.
I know this is a very uncomfortable discussion but that’s why we need to talk about it. It’s important for women to get as much information as possible so they can make the best possible choices for themselves. It’s important for all women to be heard and to never dismiss what they have to say and their experience. That’s why I’m making this post to make it possible for women to be heard on my page, both women who have experienced BII but also women who have positive experiences with breast augmentation. Open and honest communication is the best way for us to care for ourselves and each other.  Please share your story in comments below. #bii #breastimplantillness

An abdominoplasty is most commonly referred to as a “tummy tuck.” This is a plastic surgery procedure that modifies the appearance of the abdomen, making it look flatter, tighter, slimmer, and more contoured.  Studies also show that it improves back pain, improves core strength, and improves pelvic floor Support.

According to the ASPS (American Society of Plastic Surgeons), about 130,000 tummy tucks are performed in the U.S. every year, making it an extremely common procedure!

One of the largest tummy tuck flaps I have ever removed weighed almost 9 and a half pounds (4.3 kg) and measured about 1 and a half feet long (45cm). My patient had lost over 70 pounds through diet and exercise resulting in a lot of excess skin.  It was a privilege to be able to participate in her life changing transformation ❤️ 

When I perform tummy tuck surgery, I take into consideration all the little details – keeping scars thin, low and symmetric, creating a “signature natural-looking belly button,” and shaping the waist and abdomen to create the appearance of abs while keeping curves.  My meticulous and gentle technique also has minimal scarring with a nearly invisible suture line.  I am also very gentle so my patients have a quick recovery and little to no pain or bruising.  I know it sounds hard to believe but follow my patients’ journeys on my daily IG stories to see with your own eyes🙂.

If you have any questions about this procedure please ask away in comments below. 

Contact my office to schedule your consultation with me and start your plastic surgery journey. @surgeon

node.text:
I believe in challenging stereotypes so all girls can feel free to be themselves and know that with dedication and hard work anything is possible.
You will constantly get opinions about how to act, how to dress, how to be and then another set of opinions telling you just the opposite.  One thing that I noticed early in life, even before my medical career, was that people disapproved of my ways of doing things regardless if I followed my own ideas or social norms so I figured I might as well live the way that I found my life to be the most fulfilling. Nowadays I barely notice because I’ve chosen to notice what matters in life. Therefore, my advice is to choose to be you, to never go into hiding, and to start focusing on positivity and love from those who support you. Focus on your strengths and celebrate your successes and what you want to accomplish. Don't be afraid to be yourself.  When you are true to yourself, it will allow you to be unaffected from any negative judgments. 

#freeyourmind #modelsurgeon
